<p><a name="Written_references" id="Written_references"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=James_Stockdale&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Written references">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Written references</span></h3>
<p>Apart from the works written by Stockdale himself, the following work refers extensively to Stockdale's involvement in the Tonkin Gulf:</p>
<ul>
<li>Edwin E. Moise, <i>Tonkin Gulf and the Escalation of the Vietnam War</i> UNC Press North Carolina 1996 <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0807823007" class="internal">ISBN 0-8078-2300-7</a></li>
</ul>
<p>The following book is based on the series of lectures delivered for the course in moral philosophy established at the Naval War College by Admiral Stockdale in 1978, when Stockdale was president of the college. The course was designed by Stockdale and Professor Joseph Brennan, who continued to teach it after Stockdale retired from the Navy. The Foreword was written by Stockdale.</p>
<ul>
<li>Joseph Gerard Brennan, FOUNDATIONS OF MORAL OBLIGATION: The Stockdale Course, Presidio Press, Novato, California (1994) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0891415289" class="internal">ISBN 0-89141-528-9</a></li>
</ul>
